          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Finish the butter bean purée</strong></p>\n<p>Drain and rinse the <strong>butter beans</strong> and add them to a <strong>food processor</strong>.</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Go easy!) with the juice of 1/4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1/2]</span> <strong>lemon</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>.</p>\n<p>Blitz until smooth – this is your<strong> butter bean pureé</strong>.</p>\n<p>Tip: If you don't have a food processor, you can mash the beans instead.</p>",
